<br>
<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mithrull</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I've seen more weird things with this quest. Was helping someone else finish this tonight. She turns in the harness to Broodmother and gets agro from some wurms but the BM seems undisturbed and makes her way to Giant fort. Now in my other times with this quest, Fergul and the other named will despawn and respawn and then make their way to the front of the fort and sort of 'wait' there for the BM to arrive. You can't kill Fergul until the BM starts to attack the other Giant and Fergul makes his way for the zone. This time though, Fergul and his friend walk, not run,  right out of the Giant fort and start roaming around near us. We start backing away to avoid agro but they eventually find someone to attack and then all hell breaks loose. First time I've ever seen Fergul and the other named walk out of the fort and start wandering. Any explanations?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ejkas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I cannot explain why Fergul would roam about after leaving the fort. As far as aggroing wurms and not the Broodmother, this happens at all times, not exclusive to the quest. The BM doesn't assist other wurms. <P>I have also seen all sorts of odd stuff happen with this quest.<BR>The Broodmother never climbs the slope to the fort, she simply wanders about the zone for 20-30 minutes and poofs<P>The giants despawn, respawn and don't walk out<P>The quest runs as it should, and then loops. The Broodmother doesn't despawn, and the quest restarts each time Fergul spawns. <P>The Broodmother becomes a pet<P>The Broodmother heads south to Vores the Hunter, and poofs<P>Fergul's friend doesn't join him outside the fort. Fergul just waits around, and BM never attacks.<P>All sorts of strange things have happened with this quest. The only beneficial bug Ive experienced was with the quest looping. Managed to get a total of 13 leggings in 2 days over the course of 9 hours.<P>Things go wrong more often then they go right. The leggings are just slightly worse than EM greaves, and IMO its worth doing the quest over when it breaks.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually had this happen the correct way, some weird spawn way and well the wrong way.<P>Correct - follow the quest spoiler on Allakhazam<P>Weird Spawn Way - we got 2 Fergul's. BM starts to kill one giant (they should really think about SoW on this BM) he dies.  We kill off one giant (no legs).  BM starts on other and so do we.  We get attacked but kill the giant first and the get the legs - BM poofs<P>Wrong Way - we killed the wrong giant.  We killed the right one after that and got attacked by BM.  We still got the legs<P><P>------------------<BR>Hugs,<BR>Torriana Shaddowfists<BR>Loving Wife of Curius Shaddowfists<BR>60th Cleric<BR>Brell Serillis Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109127" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kaharz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This has got to be one of the most screwed up quests I've ever seen.  It seems to break at random and get bugged in random ways.  One of my druid friends has tried it twice.  First time he used the harness of control and absolutey nothing happened.  The BM just acted like he had given her some junk item.  The second time I believe the BM started walking around but the giants didn't show or something.  Thank Brell I skipped this step in upgrading my equipement.  Went straight from gold legs to Gladiator chain.<P>Kaharz Stronginthearm<BR>54th lvl cleric of Brell<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR>Forsaken<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
